post_Description:
scaled and icy was created and born in a time of uncertainty.
live shows were always an important part of our dna as a band. we probably wouldnâ€™t even exist with out them. we always wrote songs for the show, never the other way around. but i always wondered what it would be like to write a record that never existed in a concert setting.
then we had no choice but to write that kind of record. so thatâ€™s what we tried.
as the songs took shape, and we released them, and sat at home, we felt proud. proud of our fans, mostly. it felt good to release music. but something was off. i wondered, what would happen to these songs if we let them echo through a venue?
and then, slowly, live music began to dust itself off.

71 shows and 14 countries later, scaled and icy became something different. the lyrics meant something different, something more, the colors found their purpose, the chords rubbed together differently. the record came to life.
it was confirmed: this band and these specific songs needed live music.

i want to thank our crew, who took us around the world during one of the toughest eras of touring ever.
this past album cycle has meant so much to me.
and you, you resilient bunch of my favorite people, you brought this to life and continue to support it. you have given me purpose, humility, and pride. you guys have given me so much. thank you.

and that concludes Ïˆ

In this one of a kind video, captured during a safari in South Africa's greater Kruger area in February 2023, a group of tourists found themselves unexpectedly caught up in a dramatic scene involving a herd of elephants. Initially, the atmosphere was calm as the visitors enjoyed observing the relaxed elephants. However, the tranquility was shattered when a young female elephant suddenly t-boned her brother, causing him to fall onto his back and cry out for assistance.

In response, the mother elephants rushed to the young one's aid, but in the chaos, they mistakenly perceived the tourists and their vehicle as the source of the disturbance. This misunderstanding led to a tense standoff between the protective elephants and the safari guide. Fortunately, the experienced guide managed to diffuse the situation and reassure the agitated herd, averting any potential danger.

Ultimately, everyone emerged from the encounter unscathed, although the young elephant that was knocked over likely suffered some bruises from the unexpected tumble.

Patterning

ğŸ“½ by @Paulyk5

Demonstrating a keen awareness of its prey's behavior, the coyote seizes every opportunity to stealthily close the distance between itself and the target.

Patterning refers to the process by which a predator observes and analyzes the behavior, movements, and habits of its prey to determine the most opportune moment to strike. By studying the target's patterns, predators can anticipate their movements, minimize the risk of detection, and increase their chances of a successful hunt.

Humans use pattern recognition as well. As an essential aspect of their training, boxers examine their opponentâ€™s previous fights to observe their fighting style, studying up on their strengths and weaknesses in order to develop a strategic game plan to exploit any perceived vulnerabilities to increase their chances of victory.

Unlike human athletes who can study their opponents' patterns in a video analysis room, predators in the wild, such as the coyote, must learn these skills through direct experience in their natural environment. Driven by the relentless force of hunger, these creatures have no choice but to quickly adapt and develop their hunting tactics, transforming themselves into formidable hunters in the unforgiving world of nature.

post_Description:
Elegant Destruction

ğŸ“½ by @thesecretlifeofconnor

Elephants, known for their incredible strength and large size, have various reasons for knocking over trees. These powerful herbivores consume a significant amount of vegetation daily, and toppling trees grants them access to otherwise unreachable leaves, twigs, bark, and uprooted tree roots. Their strength is exemplified by their versatile trunk, which contains over 40,000 muscles and can lift up to 700 pounds (approximately 317 kg). Additionally, their massive size and muscular build enable them to exert immense force when necessary.

Another reason elephants knock over trees is to create open spaces for easier movement and social interactions within their herd. These spaces also generate new habitats and food sources for other species, making elephants a keystone species in their ecosystems. Furthermore, they may push over trees to access minerals in the soil or hidden water sources beneath the roots, particularly during times of drought.

Tree-knocking can also serve as a form of communication and dominance display within the herd or to intimidate potential threats. Elephants may push against trees to scratch themselves, remove parasites, and shed old skin. To knock over large trees, they employ a combination of their body weight, trunk, and tusks, exerting a substantial amount of force.

Although tree-knocking is a natural behavior for elephants, it can lead to deforestation and habitat destruction when their population density becomes too high in a specific area.

Rerouting

Moose sends a dogsledding couple offroading

I donâ€™t know enough about moose to tell you exactly what triggered this hostile response, but I have seen similar clips and if I had to guess, I would say it has everything to do with the dogs.

But why?

When we look at a dogsled, we just see sled dogs, but when moose look at a dogsled, they see a group of medium-sized canids that look an awful lot like wolves. Considering that dogs and wolves are very closely related, plus the fact that moose have evolved alongside wolves over years and years and know that they represent true existential danger, it's not really a huge stretch to say that this is an instinctual reaction to a perceived threat.

Again, Iâ€™m talking out of my butthole here. These are just my thoughts

In general, moose are not aggressive animals, but they can become defensive and dangerous if they feel threatened or cornered.

Some of you might be wondering about the status of the dogs and the people involved, and I can tell you that while everyone was understandably shaken (with the exception of the guy with the camera - he sounds like he's bored) , they all made it home unscathed.

post_Description:
Turf War

ğŸ“½ by @andrediving

Moray eel and a octopus fight over a hiding spot

Looking for a place to hang out isn't always as simple as finding a spot and parking your ribbonesque anatomy inside of it. Sometimes your spot of choice is already occupied.

This is precisely what is happening here, and even though the octopus technically has dibs on this primo spot, it is the moray who wins this fight in the end - tearing the tenacious octopusâ€™ arm off and eating it for good measure.

Not to worry: When an octopus loses one of its arms, it has the amazing ability to grow it back by regenerating the tissue. After the arm is lost, special cells at the injury site, called blastema cells, start to multiply and form a small lump. These cells act like a construction crew, working together to rebuild the missing arm.

The blastema cells transform into different types of cells that make up the new arm, such as muscle cells, nerve cells, and skin cells. This process is guided by signals in the octopus's body that tell the cells where to go and what to become. It takes some time for the arm to fully regrow, and although the new limb might look just like the original, it may not be as strong or flexible.

This process of tissue regeneration does require a significant amount of energy. The octopus must allocate resources, such as proteins, fats, and sugars to fuel the growth and development of the new limb. This energy is used by the blastema cells to multiply, differentiate into various cell types, and ultimately rebuild the lost structure.

During the regrowth process, the octopus might need to consume more food to meet its increased energy demands. Despite the energy expenditure, the ability to regrow a limb provides the octopus with a significant survival advantage in its challenging marine environment.

Just The Tip

Raccoon takes advantage of a cold stunned iguana

When the temperature drops below 50Â°F (10Â°C), iguanas, which are cold-blooded reptiles, can become "cold stunned". This is a physiological response in which their body temperature drops and they become immobile or sluggish. In extreme cases, they may appear dead.

Cold stunned iguanas are relatively common in Florida, where these lizards have been introduced and are not native to the environment. During cold snaps, iguanas may fall from trees or become immobilized on the ground. They are not necessarily dead, but they may be in a state of shock.

As a defense mechanism to evade predators, iguanas have the ability to detach their tails. Because this part of their body is considered â€œexpendableâ€ the nerve endings in their tails are not as sensitive as within the rest of their body. This reduced sensitivity allows them to take tail damage without stressing as much about it.

Not saying the iguana canâ€™t feel this, but the combination of cold stun and reduced sensitivity in the tail might be the reason the iguana looks like he can't be bothered in response to being gnawed on by this trash panda.

Body Shots

ğŸ“½ by @pacificoffshore

â€œOrcas rarely use their teeth to kill prey. Most of the time a combination of body-slamming, head-butting and slaps from the tail are used to inflict blunt force trauma. While this is no doubt a sad video in some respects, this is the way of the Orca. One dolphin fed the entire pod of five for at least one whole day.â€ - Ryan Lawler

Orcas are the largest members of the dolphin family, so while larger â€œkiller whaleâ€ dolphins killing and eating a smaller member of their extended family might seem strange, and some might be tempted to call this behavior cannibalistic, it is normal behavior and definitely not cannibalism.

Cannibalistic behavior refers to the act of consuming the flesh or organs belonging to a member of your own species. If a human eats a human, that's cannibalism. If a killer whale eats another killer whale, that's cannibalism. Members of the same taxonomic rank consuming each other is not considered cannibalism because even though they are classified within the same â€œfamilyâ€ they are different species.

POLLO E PATATE IN PADELLA
Pochi ingredienti e una ricetta semplice per un secondo saporito e sostanzioso, perfetto anche come piatto unico per una cenetta in famiglia ğŸ˜˜

INGREDIENTI

1,2kg pollo in pezzi
1,2kg patate
1/2 bicchiere vino bianco
4 spicchi aglio
rosmarino fresco q.b.
olio extravergine dâ€™oliva q.b.
sale fino q.b.

PROCEDIMENTO

In un tegame bello capiente mettiamo un poâ€™ dâ€™olio e sistemiamo il pollo, cercando di non sovrapporre i pezzi. Mettiamo anche dei rametti di rosmarino e due spicchi dâ€™aglio interi e vestiti. Accendiamo il fornello e facciamo rosolare bene la carne, girandola dopo qualche minuto per far dorare entrambi i lati poi sfumiamo con  il vino bianco. Una volta evaporato il vino, chiudiamo con il coperchio e facciamo cuocere per una mezzâ€™ora circa, mescolando di tanto in tanto.
Mentre il pollo cuoce, occupiamoci delle patate: peliamole, laviamole e tagliamole a cubetti di medie dimensioni.
Quando il pollo Ã¨ quasi cotto, aggiustiamo di sale e lasciamo il coperchio a soffietto per far evaporare un poâ€™ del liquido di cottura e far rosolare la carne a puntino. Una volta ben rosolato il pollo, spegniamo e togliamolo dal tegame mettendolo da parte (togliamo anche lâ€™aglio e il rosmarino).
Nello stesso tegame mettiamo le patate, poi aggiungiamo un poâ€™ di rosmarino (questa volta spezzettato) e due spicchi dâ€™aglio a pezzetti. Riaccendiamo il fuoco, diamo una bella mescolata e facciamo cuocere per circa 15 minuti, dopo aver aggiustato di sale e coperto con il coperchio. Quando sono pronte le patate, rimettiamo in pentola anche il pollo, mescoliamo e lasciamo insaporire tutto insieme per 3-4 minuti.
Pronto! Portiamo in tavola il nostro pollo e patate in padella bello fumante eâ€¦ buon appetito!

GNOCCHI DI ZUCCHINE
Una variante dei classici gnocchi, facili da fare e versatili ğŸ˜˜

INGREDIENTI

250g zucchine
250g ricotta
1 uovo
1 cucchiaio formaggio grattugiato
250g farina 00
noce moscata q.b.
sale fino q.b.

PROCEDIMENTO

Iniziamo a preparare i nostri gnocchi di zucchine grattugiando in una ciotola la zucchina. Saliamo e lasciamola insaporire qualche minuto.
Nel frattempo, in unâ€™altra ciotola mettiamo la ricotta, lâ€™uovo, il formaggio grattugiato, un pizzico di sale e un poâ€™ di noce moscata. Amalgamiamo bene tutto con una forchetta. Aggiungiamo le zucchine ben strizzate, in modo da eliminare tutta lâ€™acqua che avranno rilasciato, e mescoliamo. Iniziamo ad aggiungere la farina, un poâ€™ alla volta e continuando a mescolare. Quando lâ€™impasto prende consistenza, continuiamo a lavorarlo sul piano, aggiungendo ancora un poâ€™ di farina se necessario.
Una volta pronto lâ€™impasto (dovrÃ  essere omogeneo e morbido ma non troppo appiccicoso) stendiamolo leggermente con il mattarello. Con un coltello tagliamolo in tante strisce e poi arrotondiamole con le mani. Tagliamo le â€œcodeâ€ ottenute in tanti pezzetti, per dar forma agli gnocchi.
Lessiamo gli gnocchi in acqua bollente salata. Scoliamoli dopo pochi minuti, non appena tornano a galla. Poi condiamo i nostri gnocchi di zucchine come piÃ¹ preferiamo e portiamoli in tavola belli fumanti! Possiamo farli burro e salvia: un condimento classico, delicato e profumato. Oppure conditi con una deliziosa cremina allo zafferano: un gusto ricco e avvolgente! O ancora nel modo forse piÃ¹ tradizionale: con un un bel sughetto di pomodori e basilico! Un primo perfetto per il pranzo della domenica in famiglia.

Padang (ANTARA) @antaranewscom -
Gubernur Sumatera Barat, Mahyeldi menilai film Buya Hamka sarat akan teladan, terutama bagi generasi muda tentang bagaimana cara memadupadankan agama, budaya dan ilmu ke dalam karakter pribadi untuk mencapai aktualisasi diri.

"Dalam film tersebut, kita disuguhi bagaimana sosok Buya Hamka menerapkan pemahaman agama, budaya dan ilmu ke dalam karakternya untuk menjadi pribadi yang dihormati dan disegani," katanya di Padang, Sabtu.
 
Ia menyebutkan bahwa tidak banyak orang yang memiliki karakter seperti Buya Hamka, yang dikenal sebagai seorang ulama, penulis, filsuf, pengajar, cendekiawan dan politikus.
 
"Sangat pantas rasanya, jika sosoknya menjadi teladan bagi banyak orang. Buya Hamka adalah inspirasi dan teladan yang maafnya tidak bertepi, toleransinya tak tertandingi dan ilmunya seluas bumi," katanya.
 
Ia mengajak masyarakat "Minang", terutama generasi muda untuk beramai-ramai menonton film Buya Hamka pada bulan April nanti.
 
"Saya berharap, masyarakat Sumbar dapat beramai-ramai menonton film ini nantinya. Jadilah kisah perjuangan Buya Hamka tersebut sebagai inspirasi kita semua," kata Mahyeldi.

Just in time for the weekend, cherry trees in Washington DC have reached peak bloom! The blooming of the cherry trees around the Tidal Basin has come to symbolize the natural beauty of our nation's capital city. The famous trees, a gift of Japan in 1912, signal Washington's beginning of spring with an explosion of life and color that surrounds the Tidal Basin in a sea of pale pink and white blossoms.

You can help us preserve cherry trees! Protecting trees happens at the roots, branches, and blossoms. Leaving blossoms on the trees - even on the ground! - is critical for the tree's interactions with pollinators like bees. Being gentle with the branches by not swinging or climbing keeps the trees strong and whole. Walking around roots keeps the soil loose enough for water to absorb, and protects the tree's roots.

Many visitors to national parks today collect passport stamps, magnets, patches, t-shirts, or other memorabilia to recall their trip and to show others where theyâ€™ve been. In the 1920s and 1930s the â€œmust haveâ€ souvenirs werenâ€™t created to be collected at all. National Park Service windshield stickers served a practical administrative purpose; they were evidence that the automobile license fees due at some parks had been paid. Americans embraced the stickers' colorful, artistic designs, sparking a collecting craze. Drivers pasted so many to their windshields they quickly became a safety hazard. The stickers were reduced in size and eventually phased out. After WWII, the first self-adhesive bumper stickers were created in 1946, and visitors had a new way to decorate their cars and show off where theyâ€™ve been.

Learn more about the sticker craze by clicking the link in our bio.

post_Description:
I have no misconceptions about love. I have seen too many romantic movies and read too many fairytales to know that love is not a simple 'happily ever after'. i don't think that all you need is to find 'the one' and everything else will fall into place.

Honestly, I have no idea why people relate love to this magical feeling where someone is all starry-eyed and doting and neither one can do anything wrong.

Because this whole idea that love is perfection and love is calm waters is a horrible way to introduce someone to what loving you could feel like.

I'm human. I will make mistakes. And you and I are so very different. There will be times when we just simply cannot agree with one another, there will be times when one of us is wrong, and in those times what will you think about love? Will you consider yourself having fallen out of love? Because of course you will have an argument, of course there will be tears and a feeling that they don't understand you at all, so what now? do you just give up?

Because that's the kind of love we are being taught. The kind that makes you question the bad times, the kind that give you no room to be angry or make a mistake or call someone out on something they did, because if you do then according to the standards set by "romantic notions" you couldn't possibly be in love.

But you are, you know you are. and that's why all this stuff feels so wrong.

Love is supposed to be everything including the bad times, especially the bad times. Because when you love someone, really love someone, even when you fight you're always on the same team.
__

written by @artalanche_ridhigupta for The Scribbled Stories

post_Description:
it is not easy to open up. it is not a cakewalk to let someone know your depths. it might seem like conversations are easy, but finding the right person to have them with is not.

it takes courage to step out of the cage your mind has trapped you in, and it takes trust to believe that someone out there is worth stepping out for. so no matter how important it is to share, it is equally scary.

efforts decide where the mind wants to rest. efforts are valuable, it is needed, but at the same time, it is seldom appreciated. the give and take process is what confuses us all. the measurements of how much to put in and accept can cost people their relationships, friendships and peace of mind.

but we all learn, donâ€™t we? we all grow with experience and get better with realisations. hurting and getting hurt always go hand in hand. you just have to decide what affects you more.

for once, let people make you feel valued. for once, hold back and give in to the endless possibilities that life has planned for you. for once, donâ€™t decide how you want to see it going, but just let it flow. for once, put in your efforts in taking time to open up. for once, just for once, do what you feel like and not what you think people might like.

you decide your own worth by how you let people treat you. look out for those who truly want to stay for you.
___

written by @justmusingsandcoffee for The Scribbled Stories

This is called a vietnamese pizza and I was so intrigued to try it when I learned about it from @nutritionbykylie and @myhealthydish because you only need 3 ingredients and 5 minutes. ğŸ™Œ
INGREDIENTS
1 rice paper
2 teaspoons chili oil
1 egg
1 tablespoon sliced green onions or parsley
INSTRUCTIONS
1. Heat a small nonstick skillet over medium heat. Add the rice paper on the dry heated skillet.
2. Once the rice paper starts to fold up, add the chili oil and one egg. Gently scramble the egg around with the chili oil until the egg is cooked. Add sliced green onions, parsley or any other toppings like kewpie mayo and/or sriracha.
3. Fold in half and serve immediately.

Did you know you can make lasagna with greek yogurt? #Sponsored I use it sometimes instead of ricotta when I want something with less fat and calories or simply when I forgot to buy ricotta. ğŸ™Œ I always have @Stonyfield Greek yogurt in my fridge to use for cooking, baking and snacking. I love that itâ€™s pesticide-free, organic and made from high-quality ingredients that I feel good about feeding to my family. #stonyfield #organic
INGREDIENTS
> For assembly
1 pound lasagna sheets
2 cups shredded mozzarella cheese
> Meat Sauce
1 tablespoon olive oil
1 pound lean ground beef
1 onion chopped
2 garlic cloves minced
1 28- ounce can crushed tomatoes
Â½ cup tomato paste
1 tablespoon Italian seasoning
1 teaspoon salt
Â½ teaspoon black pepper
> Greek Yogurt Sauce
1 Â½ cups Stonyfield Organic Greek yogurt
2 cups shredded mozzarella cheese
1 cup shredded parmesan cheese
1 egg
Â¼ cup chopped fresh basil plus more for garnish
Â½ teaspoon salt
Â½ teaspoon black pepper
INSTRUCTIONS
Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Cook lasagna sheets in boiling water until al dente, for about 8 minutes. Drain the pasta, and rinse with cold water. Set aside.
To make the meat sauce, heat the olive oil over medium heat in a large deep skillet. Add the ground beef, onions and garlic, season with Italian seasoning, salt and pepper, and cook until beef is well browned, about 10 minutes. Add the crushed tomatoes and tomato paste. Simmer until the sauce is thickened, 10 more minutes. Set aside.
Preheat the oven to 375ËšF
In a large bowl, combine the yogurt, cheeses, egg, basil, salt and pepper.
To assemble, add 1 cup of the meat sauce to a 9x13 baking dish and spread evenly. Arrange 4 cooked lasagna sheets on top. Layer 1/3 of the Greek yogurt mixture and 1/3 of the remaining meat sauce. Continue for 2 more layers, and finish with lasagna sheets topped with the meat sauce and the remaining cheese.
Cover with foil and bake in the preheated oven for 30 minutes. Remove the foil, and bake for an additional 20 minutes or until the cheese is golden and bubbly. Let rest for 15 minutes before cutting.

If you like snickers, youâ€™re going to love these date snickers made with just four ingredients. ğŸ« Iâ€™m obsessed and canâ€™t wait to make another batch of these! Inspired by @moribyan

INGREDIENTS
12 medjool dates
Â¼ cup peanut butter
Â¼ cup chopped roasted peanuts
4 ounces dark chocolate bar, cut into chunks
INSTRUCTIONS
1. Use a small sharp knife to cut a slit in each date lengthwise. Remove the pits.
2. Fill each date with 1 teaspoon peanut butter and add 1 teaspoon of crushed peanuts on top. Set aside.
3. Place the chocolate in a microwave-safe bowl. Place the bowl in the microwave at 30 second intervals. Stir chocolate in between each 30 seconds until all chocolate is melted.
4. Place a toothpick inside each stuffed date and dip the date in the melted chocolate. Use a spoon to coat the date completely in the chocolate, then allow any excess chocolate to drip off.
5. Transfer the chocolate covered date to a tray or plate lined with parchment. Sprinkle the top with the remaining crushed peanuts.
6. Place the dates in the fridge to allow the chocolate to set, about 10 minutes.

"Since my childhood, I have always made works with polka dots. Earth, moon, sun and human beings all represent dots; a single particle among billions." â€”Yayoi Kusama

Happy birthday to Yayoi Kusama, born in 1929 in Matsumoto, Nagano Prefecture, Japan!

After arriving in New York in June 1958, Kusama began a series of patterned monochrome paintings called "Infinity Nets." She filled the canvases with small, arched paint strokes that emerged as specks and dots.

Kusama has said that the dots reflect her desire to "predict and measure the infinity of the unbounded universe, from my own position in it." She also imbued the works with psychological content, describing them as realizations of a hallucination of being suffocated by nets.

post_Description:
Although James Rosenquist avoids storytelling and explicit narrative, his paintings are full of meaning. Like a good poem, a Rosenquist painting asks you to seek out information.

The fragmented images and strange juxtapositions of objects serve to increase the possibilities for multiple meanings and levels of interpretation. The abrupt color changes and scale disrupt the process of recognition and are filled with contradictions that suggest metaphors rather than specific stories.

Like complex poetry, Rosenquistâ€™s paintings require time. Unlike advertising images, they cannot be taken in at a glance.
___

Ana Mendieta's work revolves around the body, nature, and spiritual connections between them. A Cuban exile, Mendieta came to the United States in 1961, leaving much of her family behindâ€”a traumatic cultural separation that impacted her art.

Her Silueta series (begun in 1973) used a typology of abstracted feminine forms through which she hoped to access an "omnipresent female force." Working in Iowa and Mexico, she carved and shaped her figure into the earth, with arms overhead to represent the merger of earth and sky, floating in the water to symbolize the minimal space between land and sea, or with arms raised and legs together to signify a wandering soul.

Three people have died, and four others have had their eyeballs removed because of rare bacterial infections linked to contaminated eyedrops, according to the CDC.

The agency has identified 68 patients in 16 states with Pseudomonas aeruginosa, a type of bacterium resistant to most antibiotics. Eight patients have lost vision in at least one of their eyes. Some have had to undergo corneal transplants.

The project of the house of the AlfÃ©rez Gorge takes its origin from the concept of a cabin and the romantic idea of a protective shelter in the middle of the forest; an isolated house seeking to resemble an object that would have been deposited on the ground, among the trees.

The configuration is developed in semi-levels around a double height, with high windows and skylights on the roof. The high volume of its double height allows to distribute the light in all interior spaces, and compensate for the loss of windows on the first floor that protects us from any intrusion.

A moonshot for affordable housing is here. ICON, the global leader in construction-scale 3D printing, has launched Initiative 99, a global architecture competition to reimagine affordable housing. With a $1M prize fund, architects, designers and dreamers are called to help design accessible, beautiful and dignified homes that can be built for under $99k. Registration for the competition opens in the summer of 2023 and architects from all over the world including firms, individuals, and university students are encouraged to participate. ICON is committed to building a selection of the winning designs from the multi-phase, year-long competition. @icon3dtech

Thanks to the frameless sliding doors by @skyframe_global, the Haus am VierwaldstÃ¤ttersee offers a stunning panoramic view of Lake Lucerne and the Swiss Alps. Ludwig Mies van der Rohe inspired the building owner, who wanted as few walls as possible to create an unbounded spatial experience with spectacular vistas. Today, the entire front can be opened - each nine metres wide. "For me, it's like sitting in a convertible," says the owner. The minimalist furnishings with a few noble design pieces further enhance the impression of openness and lightness.

Sky-Frame windows create an unbounded spatial experience with spectacular vistas | Sky-Frames pure appearance sides with the distinct design language of Mies van der Rohe

post_Description:
The stoneware piece 'Shallow Dish' by Ewen Henderson is part of a curated selection of artworks at the newly-opened CASA LOEWE Dubai presented alongside our latest collections.

Henderson is an important figure in British art and culture known for his radicalisation of ceramics and free approach to creating without formulas or methodologies.

Henderson defied typical stylistic categorisations of classic vases or tea bowls, choosing instead to fuse multiple types of clays, glazes, and stains. This often ensued with a unique patchwork, as shown in the piece at CASA LOEWE Dubai. Moving away from the wheel, Henderson preferred using his hands to achieve unique forms that pushed everyday utilitarian objects into abstractions. Often exploring the visual connection between landscape and ceramics, his works like Shallow Dish result as ancient looking artefacts, a sort of contemporary relic built of clay, one of the oldest of earthâ€™s materials yet played with by a modern artist.

Ewen Henderson
Shallow Dish, stoneware

Dubai Mall, Fashion Avenue, Ground Floor

#LOEWE
#LOEWEdubai

post_Description:
The tapestry 'White Horse' by John Allen is part of a curated selection of artworks at the newly-opened CASA LOEWE Dubai presented alongside our latest collections.

Allen is a British artist known for his richly hued tapestries of abstracted landscapes. His bright colourful vistas offer vibrant views knitted through meticulous craftsmanship. Having collaborated with Jonathan Anderson for a LOEWE collection in 2016, his work continues to decorate LOEWE stores worldwide with his bold, colourful images that have been reproduced onto handmade wool carpets by Spanish artisans.

At CASA LOEWE Dubai, this original tapestry unites the floor pieces, richly hued ceramic walls, and colourful objects curated across the space while exhibiting high craft as high art.

John Allen
White Horse, Hand spun and dyed woven wool

Dubai Mall, Fashion Avenue, Ground Floor

#LOEWE
#LOEWEdubai

post_Description:
The sculpture 'TRIBOLOGICAL INFORMANT' by Matthew Ronay is part of a curated selection of artworks at the newly-opened CASA LOEWE Dubai presented alongside our latest collections.

At first glance, the abstract and colourful sculptures of the New York-based artist nostalgically wink at usâ€”recalling a sort of childlike playfulnessâ€”a fusion of toy, pet, and playdoh. Yet, upon closer introspection, Ronay's artwork presents a deeper reality, drawing on various artistic influences spanning surrealism, folk-art, and mythology. A hybrid aesthetic fuses past and present, ensuing as ancient artefact and also futuristic token. Exploring the power of material objects and our relationship to them, the sculpture mimics anatomical parts, allowing the viewer to consider their body in relationship to both art and the corporeal struggle they encounter in the world. Intimate in scale and exuberant in colour, the hand-bag sized sculpture unites various forms and colours within the space.

Matthew Ronay
TRIBOLOGICAL INFORMANT, basswood, dye, gouache, flocking, plastic, steel
2018

Dubai Mall, Fashion Avenue, Ground Floor

Reposted @aerosmith #AeroHistory: March 22nd, 1977 Aerosmith releases the single â€˜Back in the Saddleâ€™.

A real bullwhip was intended to be used for the whip effects and hours were spent trying to get it to crack. The band members ended up cut up and hurt without making any progress. Eventually, the band decided the whip effects would be created by whirling a 30-foot cord from the studio, then by firing a cap gun to create the crack of the whip. When the song is performed in concert, Tyler often makes more noticeable lyrical and visible references to sex. Although the lyrics, by Tyler, were written with the simple idea of cowboys and sex, this song took on new meaning after Aerosmith reunited in 1984 and embarked on their â€˜Back in the Saddle Tourâ€™.

Today, the song remains a staple on classic rock radio and in concert. It is arguably one of the heaviest songs of Aerosmithâ€™s Top 40 singles, and is cited by rock musicians @slash and James Hetfield of @metallica as among their favorite rock songs.

Reposted @lordrarerock HAIL, WHATâ€™S THE MATTER WITH YOUR MIND - Redbone perform â€œCome and Get Your Loveâ€ live in 1974. Of thousands of acts that earned hits in the 1970s, one stands apart for all others for a unique accomplishment. Redbone, which scored a pop hit in the U.S. in 1974 with â€œCome and Get Your Love,â€ were the first Native American band to achieve a Top 5 single on the Hot 100. Redbone had taken its name from a Cajun term for multi-racial individuals or culture and the members of Redbone drew from Yaqui, Shoshone, and Mexican heritage as well with roots in Texas, Louisiana and California. The groupâ€™s core musicians, brothers Patrick and Candido â€œLollyâ€ Vasquez-Vegas, were born in Coalinga, Calif. (near Fresno), moved to Los Angeles in 1959 and performed for a decade on the club scene as Pat and Lolly Vegas before founding Redbone. Their guitarist, pianist and vocalist was Robert Anthony Avila, though he went by the stage name Tony Bellamy.

When â€œCome and Get Your Loveâ€ was released as a single on Epic Records in January 1974, a longer version had been previously available on the groupâ€™s fifth studio album, 1973â€™s Wovoka. The genre-defying groupâ€™s multi-cultural musical blend of swamp funk, Tex-Mex, R&B, soul, Native American tribal heartbeats, hummable melodies, gelled into a pure pop masterpiece. (When the song peaked on April 13, 1974, other singles in the Top 10 included Blue Swedeâ€™s cover of â€œHooked on a Feeling,â€ Elton Johnâ€™s â€œBennie and the Jets,â€ and John Denverâ€™s â€œSunshine on My Shoulders.â€)

The single was certified RIAA platinum, signifying sales of a million copies and entered the pantheon of perennial pop radio standards and classics. Enjoy iiii]; )'

Reposted @lordrarerock IT AINâ€™T ME - Recently unearthed footage of Creedence Clearwater Revivalâ€™s storming set at Royal Albert Hall in London - 1970. This footage was initially thought to be long lost, however, it was recently uncovered and is being released in its entirety. CCRâ€™s show at RAH is the stuff of legend. This night captured the California band just as their creativity and popularity were peaking. Much of John Fogertyâ€™s songwriting resonated heavily with disaffected youth and their popularity was skyrocketing with the success of the album â€œGreen River,â€ which was released the previous year. This amazing footage is a special as itâ€™s the only concert footage of the original CCR lineup in its entirety.

This is an antiestablishment song of defiance and blue-collar pride, both anti-Washington and against the Vietnam War. John Fogerty and Doug Clifford both enlisted in the Army Reserves in 1966 (to avoid being drafted and shipped to Vietnam) and were discharged in 1968 after serving their military commitments. â€œThe song speaks more to the unfairness of class than war itself,â€ Fogerty said. â€œItâ€™s the old saying about rich men making war and poor men having to fight them.â€

This is one of those songs that came together very quickly. Fogerty recalled to American Songwriter magazine in January 2013: â€œWhen I felt it was about ready to hatch, I went into my bedroom and just sat down to write. The whole thing happened in about 20 minutes. That just poured out.â€ Enjoy

Reposted @stanwinstonschool Pumpkinhead - From Concept to Creation - Stan Winston's Directorial Debut.

Stan Winston made his directorial debut with PUMPKINHEAD, a low-budget horror film about a man, Ed Harley (Lance Henriksen), who conjures a mythical demon to avenge the death of his son. Originally, producers from the DeLaurentiis Entertainment Group (DEG), the film's production company, had sent Winston the script hoping to engage Stan Winston Studio to create the 'Pumpkinhead' demon. But Winston quickly recognized that, in Pumpkinhead, he had found an ideal property for his film directing debut. "It was a small picture, something I thought I could handle as a director; and I felt there was a lot that I could bring to the story. So I told the producers, 'Yeah, I'll do the creature â€” but only if I can direct the movie.'"

Meet Katmai the sea otter. ğŸ¦¦ğŸ§Š
"Well...as long as she is doing it with ice" is a common catch phrase when watching Katmai.
Video by: @rnaqua
.
Sea otters are very well known for the fact that they are one of the few species that have learned to use tools. Most often Sea otters will utilize rocks to crack open their prey and have even been known to carry a rock in their pocket.

Researchers have studied Sea otters focusing on this skill and have discovered that there is a variety of tool use across and within Sea otter populations. The amount of tool use is very dependent on ecological factors like what kind of prey is around, but it was also noted that it was influenced by individuals learning to use tools. Aka if Katmai learns something fun like she can use a tool to break something, the likelihood of all the others learning it grows ğŸ˜‚
.
Info from @rnaqua & "Variation in the frequency of tool use across and within otter populations"  Jessica A Perry

post_Description:
AAA - The Not So Average WereWolves
There were better teams than us on paper right after the auction but as they say, A sheet of paper is never enough to decide the final outcome.
Picture this - it's like the Avengers, but instead of saving the world, they're a team of gamers who save the Playground!
We were definitely the S.H.I.E.L.D

At first, people doubted the AAA Werewolves. They were like the Guardians of the Galaxy - a ragtag group of misfits who didn't seem like they belonged together. But just like Star-Lord, Gamora, Drax, Rocket, and Groot, the Werewolves proved everyone wrong.
Gaming or entertainment, We did it all. @iamvanshajsingh and @8bit_akshu were like Mario and Luigi, taking down opponents like they were Goombas. Shadow fight and Asphalt were like our fortress.
@anirudhsharma_fit was the team's Iron Man, using his wit and charm to charm his way to victory. Be it in the villa or the gaming zone.
@rain_clements was like Thor, bringing thunder and lightning to every game night. She did an amazing roast.
But just like the Avengers, the Werewolves had their fair share of setbacks.

But then, @yesmallika & @abhi9avs joined the squad, and it was like marvel meeting DC. They were like Wonder Woman and Aquaman, bringing a fresh perspective to the team.
With their new additions, the Werewolves were like the X-Men, unstoppable and fearless. They dominated the tournament like Thanos dominated the universe.
The final was like the end game but our IRON MAN saved the day.
It might be a one point difference in the asphalt leaderboard but behind that one point was our consistent determination and grit.

And in the end, we were like the Fast and Furious crew, a family who stuck together through thick and thin.

So there you have it, folks - the story of the @aaa_werewolves @amazonminitv

Despite a 103 fever, @triggeredinsaan did it all with a smile on his face. Kudos to him and the entire playground unit for bringing together an awesome season.

After 28 days of gaming and ent, We are the deserving champions.
Oh boy, I do have a story to tell my kids

Much Love to the triggered army.
Keep supporting Keep loving.

post_Description:
Hai... kali ini Hel buat minuman segar dan nikmat yang cocok buat sajian buka puasa. Punch jeruk jelly kelapa yang super simpel buatnya pakai sirup Freiss Squash rasa jeruk. Freiss hadir dengan kemasan baru pouch autolock yang praktis sehingga mudah dituang dan tidak mudah tumpah.

Produk Freiss Pouch ini bisa kalian dapatkan di Indomaret terdekat dan E-commerce, tersedia rasa jeruk dan cocopandan, udah cocok banget buat menemani bulan puasa teman-teman. Cek lengkapnya di @rumahindofood

Resep Punch Jeruk Jelly Kelapa
By @cookingwithhel

Bahan jelly kelapa:
- Jelly kelapa 1 sachet @ 15 gr
- gula 50 gr
- santan sedang 700 ml

Bahan lain:
- Sirup Freiss Squash rasa jeruk
- Air soda sesuai selera (bisa ganti air)
- Selasih secukupnya
- Es batu

Cara buat:
- Jelly kelapa: Campur semua bahan, masak hingga mendidih, siram sedikit demi sedikit ke es batu supaya membentuk seperti kerokan kelapa. Bisa juga didiamkan hingga set lalu dikerok.
- Siapkan gelas, isi es batu, tuang sirup freiss secukupnya, berisi jelly kelapa, selasih, dan air soda.
- Sajikan

post_Description:
Hai... kali ini Hel buat minuman segar dan nikmat yang cocok buat sajian buka puasa. Punch jeruk jelly kelapa yang super simpel buatnya pakai sirup Freiss Squash rasa jeruk. Freiss hadir dengan kemasan baru pouch autolock yang praktis sehingga mudah dituang dan tidak mudah tumpah.

Produk Freiss Pouch ini bisa kalian dapatkan di Indomaret terdekat dan E-commerce, tersedia rasa jeruk dan cocopandan, udah cocok banget buat menemani bulan puasa teman-teman. Cek lengkapnya di @rumahindofood

Resep Punch Jeruk Jelly Kelapa
By @cookingwithhel

Bahan jelly kelapa:
- Jelly kelapa 1 sachet @ 15 gr
- gula 50 gr
- santan sedang 700 ml

Bahan lain:
- Sirup Freiss Squash rasa jeruk
- Air soda sesuai selera (bisa ganti air)
- Selasih secukupnya
- Es batu

Cara buat:
- Jelly kelapa: Campur semua bahan, masak hingga mendidih, siram sedikit demi sedikit ke es batu supaya membentuk seperti kerokan kelapa. Bisa juga didiamkan hingga set lalu dikerok.
- Siapkan gelas, isi es batu, tuang sirup freiss secukupnya, berisi jelly kelapa, selasih, dan air soda.
- Sajikan

Hai... kali ini Hel buat chicken wing ala resto pizza yang terkenal itu, siapa nih yang suka banget sama menu ini? Yuk buat sendiri dirumah, praktis tinggal pakai airfryer / oven

Hel pakai resep chicken wing dari youtube Devina Hermawan

Chicken wings
By @CookingwithHel

Bahan
- dada ayam 500 gr (saya pakai bagian middle wings dan wings stick)
- kecap manis 1 sdm
- saos tiram 1,5 sdm
- saos barbeque 1 sdm (bisa ganti saos tomat)
- madu 2 sdm
- saos sambal 1,5 sdm
- bubuk bawang putih 1 sdt
- kaldu jamur 1 sdt
- lada Â½ sdt
- minyak goreng 2 sdm

Cara buat
- campur semua bahan kecuali minyak goreng, aduk rata lalu marinasi selama 2 jam suhu ruang atau semalaman di kulkas
- setelah dimarinasi, masukkan minyak goreng, aduk rata
- air fryer suhu 200Â°C 15-17 menit atau hingga matang, menit ke 8 oles dengan sisa bahan marinasi dan balik ayam
- sajikan dengan saos sambal

post_Description:
Hai ... kali ini Hel buat cemilan sehat dari pisang dan oatmeal, tanpa tepung dan tanpa gula. Ini mestinya stok cemilan buat saya dan suami, ternyata malah bocil2 yang habiskan. Buat teman2 yang suka oatmeal bisa coba ya.

Cookies ini bisa disimpan dikulkas tahan 5-7 harian

Sumber resep https://joyfoodsunshine.com/banana-oatmeal-cookies/

Banana Oatmeal cookies
by @CookingwithHel

Bahan
- pisang 3 bj yg udah matang banget (ambon / cavendish)
- telur 1 butir
- pasta vanila Â½ sdt
- madu 2 sdm (sesuai selera)
- quick cooking oat 120-130 gr (biasanya dipasaran kemasan yg warna biru)
- bubuk cinnamon Â½ sdt
- garam sejumput
- chocochip 85 gr

note
- hancurkan pisangnya jangan terlalu hancur, supaya tidak berair
- bila adonan kurang padat bisa ditambah oat nya ya
- selain chocochip bisa pakai kismis, kacang2an
- oatnya bisa juga pakai yg jenis rolled oat atau yg instan

cara masak
- lumatkan pisang, masukkan telur, pasta vanila, madu, aduk
- masukkan oat, bubuk cinamon, garam, aduk
- masukkan chocochip, aduk
- ambil secukup adonan, taruh diloyang
- panggang suhu 170Â°C 12-15 menit (kalo suka kering bisa panggang lebih lama)
- tunggu 5 menit suhu ruang, baru dilepas dari loyang. Cookies nya agak lengket di loyang jadi pelan2 lepasin pakai scrapper, atau bisa alasi baking paper dulu sebelumnya

Hel pakai oven listrik dari @mito.id, teman-teman bisa dapatkan produk mito ini di shopee MITOELECTRONIC (https://shp.ee/hix5vgk)

â¤ï¸ OVEN FANTASY MITO - https://shope.ee/ArShQRNVw
ğŸ’ Kapasitas 33 L
ğŸ’ KIPAS /CONVECTION
ğŸ’ LAMPU
ğŸ’ ROTISERRIE
ğŸ’ LOW WATT 450 - 850 watt (akan menurun secara berkala)
ğŸ’ Loyang : Lebar 35 cm x 29-30 cm
ğŸ’ Bisa panggang 2 tingkat (untuk kue kering)

Perhaps we shouldn't expect complex biological functions to fit into "basic" categories? What a concept!

ğŸ’­ by the amazing @pinkmantaray.

Schuyler (@pinkmantaray) is an author, educator, speaker, and the first transgender athlete to compete in any sport on an NCAA Division 1 men's team. Follow him to continue learning and consider supporting his work or participating in one of his upcoming workshops. We appreciate you Schulyer.

Important distinction: Intersex â‰  trans. While you can be trans and intersex, they are not the same thing. The purpose of this post is not to conflate these experiences, but to remind folks that biological sex is complex. Weaponizing the concept of "basic biology" against trans folks is misguided and harmful.

Beyond awareness, intersex folks deserve access to care that validates their experiences and gives them autonomy over their bodies. 54% of intersex people experience anxiety and depression. 62% were operated on before they or their parents could give informed consent. 49% were given hormones before they or their parents could give informed consent. Why are transphobes pushing to limit access to surgery and hormones for trans folks (who have given their informed consent) while ignoring the issues facing intersex folks? End intersex surgery.

Letâ€™s talk about the label bigender! ğŸ’—ğŸ’œğŸ¤ğŸ’œğŸ’™

Bigender is an LGBTQ+ identity that describes someone who experiences two genders.

This can consist of any two genders â€” including binary genders (i.e. man or woman), as well as any genders on the non-binary spectrum.

As with all identities, every bigender experience is completely unique.

For exampleâ€¦

â–«ï¸ Some bigender people experience both genders at once, while for others, their sense of gender might shift between the two â€” and some people relate to both of these scenarios.

â–«ï¸ Some bigender people identify with the labels transgender and/or non-binary (as the label bigender technically falls within these umbrellas), while others don't. Either way is okay!

â–«ï¸ Some bigender people change their name, pronouns, and/or how they express themselves based on their shifting gender, but this is not a requirement to be valid in this identity.

If youâ€™re exploring whether bigender might be the label for you, here are some signs you might relate to â¤µï¸

ğŸ’— you have trouble categorizing your gender experience into just one label

ğŸ’œ you notice that your sense of gender changes over time

ğŸ¤ your gender identity feels more expansive than what you were taught by society

ğŸ’œ you can relate when you hear about other bigender people's experiences

ğŸ’™ your sense of gender feels connected to two different identities

ğŸ’— you simply connect to the label bigender

ğŸ‘‹ğŸ» But itâ€™s also important to rememberâ€¦

â€¦ that these are just *some* of the signs that you might be bigender.

Even if have different experiences from these, you are still valid in your identity!

And the only person with any say in who you are, and what labels you use, is YOU ğŸ¥°

Each region is guaranteed a minimum number of qualifying spots to the CrossFit Games.

Now that the Quarterfinal round is complete, the Worldwide Rankings have been recalculated and the final number of Games-qualifying spots for each Semifinal has been determined.

Lake Como, located in Northern Italy, is a beautiful destination to visit, especially in the springtime. Here are some reasons why:

1. Temperature: The weather in spring is mild and pleasant, with temperatures averaging around 20Â°C (68Â°F), making it perfect for exploring the beauty of Lake Como and the surrounding areas

2. Scenery: The scenery around Lake Como is breathtaking, and in spring, the surrounding mountain peaks still have some snow on them, adding to the view.

3. Flowers: Spring is the best time to see the flowering trees and plants in the area, making for a beautiful sight. The gardens around Villa Carlotta and Villa Balbianello are particularly stunning.

4. Fewer tourists: Spring is considered the off-season for tourist crowds. As a result, the area is less crowded, and you can enjoy the peaceful atmosphere of the Lake Como.

5. Activities: Various outdoor activities are available in spring, such as hiking, boat tours, cycling, and exploring the local towns and villages, which makes it the perfect time to plan a visit.

Overall, visiting Lake Como in spring is an ideal time for those who love nature, tranquillity, and outdoor activities, making it an unforgettable experience.

Located in the Lombardy region, it is the third-largest lake in Italy, and its shoreline stretches for over 100 miles. There are several charming towns and villages around the lake Como, including Bellagio and Varenna, each with its unique attractions and cultural offerings. You can enjoy a wide range of activities by the Lake Como, such as hiking, cycling, boating, or simply relaxing and taking in the beautiful views. Ratusan suporter Persebaya atau Bonek yang datang ke Semarang menjelang laga PSIS vs Persebaya diamankan tim Polrestabes Semarang. Para Bonek diminta turun dari truk muatan yang ditumpanginya di Jalan Pantura Demak-Semarang.

Mereka sengaja datang lebih awal dari waktu yang ditentukan. Padahal, pertandingan baru dimulai Rabu (29/3/2023) pukul 20.30 WIB.

Tim gabungan juga meminta para Bonek yang menongkrong di minimarket dan jalan protokol berpindah tempat. Pasalnya, aktivitas mereka mengganggu warga sekitar.

Polda Jawa Tengah akan menerjunkan 3.500 personel gabungan, termasuk 253 steward pertandingan. Untuk mengantisipasi kedatangan Bonek, dua dapur umum, 35 truk angkutan, dan safe house disiapkan. Persiapan dilakukan untuk menghindari kerusuhan.

Streaming 24 jam di youtube 'metrotvnews' dan website metrotvnews.com

Bus pengangkut jemaah umrah mengalami kecelakaan dan terbakar di Mekkah, Senin (27/3/2023). Sebanyak 20 orang meninggal dunia.

Kecelakaan terjadi ketika bus dalam perjalanan menuju Mekkah. Saat menuruni jembatan yang menghubungkan provinsi Asir dengan Kota Abha bus mengalami rem blong dan menabrak pembatas di ujung jembatan. Bus kemudian terbalik dan terbakar.

Berdasarkan data, sebanyak 20 orang dilaporkan meninggal dunia dan 30 orang luka-luka. Korban kecelakaan memiliki kewarganegaraan yang berbeda-beda. Namun belum ada rilis lebih detail soal identitas kebangsaan korban.

Saat ini pihak Konsulat Jenderal Republik Indonesia (KJRI) Jeddah masih mengecek ada tidaknya jemaah WNI dalam rombongan tersebut.

Streaming 24 jam di youtube 'metrotvnews' dan website metrotvnews.com

Was introduced to this new interesting app, ChatGPT. I asked the app for some quotes with "smash it" in them.

It returned me instantly with the following:

" Sure, here are some quotes with "smash it":

"Life is like a block of clay. If you want to create something beautiful, you have to smash it, shape it, and mold it with determination and perseverance."

"Life is like a glass ceiling. To reach your true potential, you have to smash it and shatter the limitations that hold you back."

"Life is like a pinata, sometimes it takes a few hits to get to the good stuff, but once you do, make sure to smash it with all your might."

"Life is like a video game, you have to face the challenges head-on and smash through the obstacles to reach the next level."

"Life is like a wall, it can either keep you trapped or protect you. If you want to break free, you have to smash through it with courage and determination."

Wow!

I find it pretty inspirational. Hope you can find one to inspire you and make your day a little bit better too.

Hujung minggu lalu, saya dipelawa oleh YB @hannahyeoh untuk menemani beliau dalam lawatan ke Pusat Kecemerlangan Sukan Paralimpik Kampung Pandan, untuk memberi motivate kepada atlet-atlet sukan negara. Saya tidak teragak-agak setuju. Kalaulah kemunculan aku bole menyembarakkan semangat para-atlit kita, apa salahnya.

Tapi saya salah. Semasa sesi berbual dan bermesra bersama atlet para negara, kita saling berkongsi pengalaman hidup, pengalaman bersukan, pengalaman training. Saya sudah salah. Bukan saya yang memberi motivasi kepada dia orang. Sepatutnya, dia orang yang memberi motivasi kepada saya. Siapakah saya berani kata training tu susah, apabila ada di kalangan kita yg tiada kaki untuk berjalan? Siapakan saya berani kata untuk putus asa, apabila ada di kalangan kita yang tidak mempunyai kaki untuk berenang, tetapi masih boleh mencapai kecermelangan mengharumkan negara?

Kawan-kawan atlet-atlet sukan negara. You all are truly hero negara. Hero of all lives. I salute u all!

Salute juga YB Hannah Yeoh ,KBS, MSN , MPM atas penyelarasan isu pegawai pengiring. Keperluan semua lapisan rakyat Malaysia dijaga !

Majulah sukan untuk negara!

K-Tip Dos âœ… and Donâ€™ts âŒ from @katpee_12, Head of Education at @bellamihairproğŸ«¡
__________

Whether youâ€™re an under or over roller, fast or slow roller, happy or sad roller, or anything in between, these are just a few universal things to remember:â£
â£
âŒDonâ€™t grab a super thick or wide section. This can cause tension and breakage. If there is too much natural hair, your extension hair will not bond and seal properly.

âŒ Donâ€™t over stretch your keratin at the top too far. When is dries, it can become uncomfortable for a guest. Just a bit pokey. Not to be confused with POKE, which is amazing ğŸ£. â£
â£
âŒDonâ€™t grab too thin of a section. You are really looking for a 1/1 ratio of natural hair to extension hair. â£
â£
âŒDonâ€™t get too close to the scalp! We always want a bit of movement out of our extensions to allow for maximum comfort the entire duration of wear. â£
â£
âŒDonâ€™t elevate your bonds!! Just like all methods, 0 elevation is key my friends! Over-direction can occur from improper shield placement or rolling at an elevated angle. Keep everything as close to the natural grow direction as possible.â£
â£
âŒDonâ€™t apply too low! K-Tips are made to live in the hair for a longer period of time. If we apply to low, then they will feel beyond grown out by the time 2 months rolls around. â£
â£
âœ…Do use your shield as a guide. Your section should not be wider than the square in the middle. â£
â£
âœ…Do make sure to seal the top and the bottom of your bond. Think: a grain of rice. ğŸš â£
â£
âœ…Do get a nice tap, wrap, and roll action happening. â£
â£
âœ…Do shape the bond and manipulate the malleable keratin into the rice shape. Try not to pinch and press too hard â€” this is what leads to boxy bonds with edges. ğŸ“¦âŒâ£
â£
âœ…Do feel free to cut and custom shape your bonds to your liking, if need be! Sometimes cutting into an arrow can give for a smoother transition from natural k-tip. Play around and see what works for you.

It all starts with a clean foundationğŸ¤Œ

Follow these 8 tips from @bellamihairpro Senior Educator @amandabrunohair to get a clean beaded foundation.
_______

The foundation is crucial and definitely one of the most important parts of a sew-in installation. The foundation maintains the health of the natural hair, longevity, and comfortability of the extension installation.

Tips:

- Use Hair Grippers to help with clean sectioning and flyaways.
- Always check the perimeter. Make sure there is enough natural hair to cover the extension when your guest ties their hair up.
- You can use a pin curl clip as a mark indicator, so you know where your anchor beads should be placed.
- Always check for crosshairs. Make sure your sectioning is very clean.
- Utilize your cutting chair when needed to be level with your section.
- Place your looping tool on your pinky so youâ€™re not having to pick up and set down your tools as often.
- Make sure you do not secure the bead too tight. This can cause tension on the natural hair and uncomfortability to your client.
- Maintain a 0Â° elevation.
